{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"39bb7176-0fb3-4ee0-956e-d0a068649c12","content":"Analyzing crash dumps is outside the scope of the tools I have available here (the `dump-collect` skill only covers **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them). However, here's how you can investigate your `.dmp` file:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of crashing thread |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Last exception details |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap overview (for OOM crashes) |\n| `threads` | List all managed threads |\n| `clrstack -all` | Stacks for all threads |\n\n**Using Visual Studio** (Windows):\n- Open the `.dmp` file directly → click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"**\n\n**Using `lldb`** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nclrstack\npe\n```\n\nWould you like help setting up dump **collection** for future crashes instead?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"da4db279-c52d-417e-af53-5defcf332586","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is explicitly not for analyzing dumps. I should not invoke it.\n\nI can help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":422,"requestId":"9812:DE08:7B818D2:8832874:69F407B8"},"id":"075d2cfe-b2c8-4fb4-beb2-60107aa2d9e8","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:54:13.071Z","parentId":"d3734037-9539-4d54-9125-be732fc3a83f"}
